  <!-- ── 9. Section 6: Methodology ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="methodology" class="py-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">6. Methodology and sources</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-lg text-body max-w-none space-y-6 text-[21px] leading-[1.7]">
        <p>This report synthesises data from six federal and nationally representative sources. All figures are drawn directly from published primary sources or calculated using disclosed methodology from those sources.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><a href="https://www.ic3.gov/annualreport/reports" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold text-ink hover:text-brand underline underline-offset-2 decoration-brand/30 hover:decoration-brand">FBI IC3 Annual Report 2024:</a> cybercrime complaint volumes and internet fraud losses.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.ftc.gov/reports/consumer-sentinel-network-data-book-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold text-ink hover:text-brand underline underline-offset-2 decoration-brand/30 hover:decoration-brand">FTC Consumer Sentinel Network Data Book 2024:</a> consumer-reported fraud, identity theft, and loss data by age and contact method.</li>
          <li><a href="https://bjs.ojp.gov/library/publications/victims-identity-theft-2021" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold text-ink hover:text-brand underline underline-offset-2 decoration-brand/30 hover:decoration-brand">BJS Victims of Identity Theft 2021 (NCJ 306474):</a> survey-based population victimisation rates from the National Crime Victimization Survey Identity Theft Supplement. The 2021 ITS questionnaire was redesigned; BJS states the data is not comparable to prior years.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.census.gov/data/tables/time-series/demo/popest/2020s-national-detail.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold text-ink hover:text-brand underline underline-offset-2 decoration-brand/30 hover:decoration-brand">US Census Bureau Vintage 2024 Population Estimates (NC-EST2024-AGESEX-RES):</a> national population denominators by age group.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.aarp.org/pri/topics/work-finances-retirement/fraud-consumer-protection/2025-fraud-survey/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold text-ink hover:text-brand underline underline-offset-2 decoration-brand/30 hover:decoration-brand">AARP 2025 Fraud Survey:</a> probability-based national sample (n=1,423, ±3.4% confidence interval) conducted via NORC AmeriSpeak, February 2025.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.fdic.gov/household-survey/2023-fdic-national-survey-unbanked-and-underbanked-households-report" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold text-ink hover:text-brand underline underline-offset-2 decoration-brand/30 hover:decoration-brand">FDIC 2023 National Survey of Unbanked and Underbanked Households:</a> used for digital banking access data only; FDIC does not measure fraud directly.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Where rates, population-level comparisons, or age-normalised metrics appear in this report, they are calculated using published denominators and identified as derived. These sources measure different dimensions of fraud and are not arithmetically addable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

